title.narrative: PROTECTION OP 3 - PREVENTION AND BEHAVIOR CHANGE

description.narrative: By 2023, children, parents and communities in target regions, in development and humanitarian settings are sensitized on social and gender norms and behaviors that are supportive of a child's right to protection from harm and prevention of gender-based violence, which contributes to Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, girls and boys in Madagascar, particularly the most vulnerable, are better protected from violence, exploitation, abuse, neglect and child marriage

description.narrative: Around 15,000 children participated in the child protection activities with UNICEF&39;s support: 300 children’s clubs in lower secondary schools in 6 regions. 10,481 children in 7 regions benefited from the national life skills programme, as did 585 parents in 2 regions. Education and awareness raising interventions on online protection reached 4,442 children, 651 parents and 214 educators.In the drought-stricken south,23,698 people (including 15,598 children) benefited from GBV risk mitigation, prevention or response interventions, including life skills, parenting skills and positive masculinity programs. 24 regional child protection actors in the Anosy region were trained to reduce child marriage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
